# Mikhmon Frontend ‚Äî PPPoE, Logs & WebSocket Real-time

Add PPPoE management pages, system/hotspot/PPP log pages, and upgrade all
monitoring panels (hotspot active, hotspot inactive, PPP active, PPP inactive)
to fetch data in real-time via WebSocket instead of HTTP polling.

## Proposed Changes

---

### Types & API Layer

#### [MODIFY] [types/index.ts](file:///home/butterfly-student/programing/Mikrotik/gomikhmon/frontend/src/types/index.ts)
- Add [PPPSecret](file:///home/butterfly-student/programing/Mikrotik/gomikhmon/backend/internal/domain/dto/ppp.go#5-23), [PPPProfile](file:///home/butterfly-student/programing/Mikrotik/gomikhmon/backend/internal/domain/dto/ppp.go#26-58), [PPPActive](file:///home/butterfly-student/programing/Mikrotik/gomikhmon/backend/internal/domain/dto/ppp.go#61-77), `PPPInactive` interfaces
- `PPPInactive` is equivalent to [PPPSecret](file:///home/butterfly-student/programing/Mikrotik/gomikhmon/backend/internal/domain/dto/ppp.go#5-23) (secrets not currently online)

#### [NEW] [api/ppp.ts](file:///home/butterfly-student/programing/Mikrotik/gomikhmon/frontend/src/api/ppp.ts)
CRUD untuk PPP secrets dan profiles, serta action disconnect (bukan data fetch ‚Äî Active/Inactive data diambil via WebSocket):
- `pppApi.getSecrets(routerId)` ‚Üí `GET /api/v1/mikrotik/:id/ppp/secrets`
- `pppApi.createSecret(routerId, data)` ‚Üí `POST`
- `pppApi.updateSecret(routerId, id, data)` ‚Üí `PUT`
- `pppApi.deleteSecret(routerId, id)` ‚Üí `DELETE`
- `pppApi.enableSecret` / `disableSecret` ‚Üí `PATCH enable/disable`
- `pppApi.getProfiles(routerId)` ‚Üí profiles CRUD (get, create, update, delete)
- `pppApi.disconnectActive(routerId, id)` ‚Üí `DELETE /ppp/active/:id` *(action kick, bukan data fetch)*

#### [NEW] [api/logs.ts](file:///home/butterfly-student/programing/Mikrotik/gomikhmon/frontend/src/api/logs.ts)
- `logsApi.getSystemLogs(routerId)` ‚Üí `GET /mikrotik/:id/logs`
- `logsApi.getHotspotLogs(routerId)` ‚Üí `GET /mikrotik/:id/logs/hotspot`
- `logsApi.getPPPLogs(routerId)` ‚Üí `GET /mikrotik/:id/logs/ppp`

---

### WebSocket Hooks

All hooks follow the same pattern as [useResourceWebSocket.ts](file:///home/butterfly-student/programing/Mikrotik/gomikhmon/frontend/src/hooks/useResourceWebSocket.ts):
auto-connect on mount, reconnect on close, cleanup on unmount.

WS URL pattern: `ws://{host}/api/v1/ws/mikrotik/monitor/{endpoint}/{routerId}?key={key}`

#### [NEW] [hooks/useHotspotActiveWS.ts](file:///home/butterfly-student/programing/Mikrotik/gomikhmon/frontend/src/hooks/useHotspotActiveWS.ts)
- Endpoint: `hotspot-active`
- Returns `{ users: HotspotActive[], isConnected, lastUpdate }`

#### [NEW] [hooks/useHotspotInactiveWS.ts](file:///home/butterfly-student/programing/Mikrotik/gomikhmon/frontend/src/hooks/useHotspotInactiveWS.ts)
- Endpoint: `hotspot-inactive`
- Returns `{ users: HotspotUser[], isConnected, lastUpdate }`

#### [NEW] [hooks/usePPPActiveWS.ts](file:///home/butterfly-student/programing/Mikrotik/gomikhmon/frontend/src/hooks/usePPPActiveWS.ts)
- Endpoint: `ppp-active`
- Returns `{ connections: PPPActive[], isConnected, lastUpdate }`

#### [NEW] [hooks/usePPPInactiveWS.ts](file:///home/butterfly-student/programing/Mikrotik/gomikhmon/frontend/src/hooks/usePPPInactiveWS.ts)
- Endpoint: `ppp-inactive`
- Returns `{ connections: PPPInactive[], isConnected, lastUpdate }`

#### [NEW] [hooks/useLogMonitorWS.ts](file:///home/butterfly-student/programing/Mikrotik/gomikhmon/frontend/src/hooks/useLogMonitorWS.ts)
- Generic hook accepting endpoint type: `'logs' | 'hotspot-logs' | 'ppp-logs'`
- Returns `{ entries: LogEntry[], isConnected }`
- Appends new log entries (up to 500 max), not replaces

